article.headline: New Orleans 65, Rollins College 57
article.story:
BAKERSFIELD, Calif. (AP) -- C.J. Massingale scored 27 points and
led Metro State to an 88-54 win over Rollins College Wednesday,
advancing the Roadrunners to the semifinals of the Division II
tournament.

Lester Strong scored 18 points and grabbed 16 rebounds for Metro
State (32-2).

Eric Faber had 17 points for Rollins (27-6) and Chad Dircks
added 12.

Metro shot over 60 percent in the first half and had a 16-point
lead at the break. The Roadrunners had 20 more rebounds than
Rollins and twice as many steals.

Keith Borgan scored 11 for Metro State while adding eight
assists. Luke Kendall had 10 points and was 3-of-4 on 3-point
attempts.

Metro State will play Southern Indiana on Thursday in the
semifinal.
